ad PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528971\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528971\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 17, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104jok1665703129463.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jok1665703129463.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jok1665703129463.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"jok1665703129463\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      trigger formatToDisplay\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">System trigger that temporarily converts the format of data in a field from an internal format into an external format that is displayed or printed.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jok1665703129463__section_w488ab1b7b1_w489ab1b7_w490ab1\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"jok1665703129463__table_d14261e1_d14262e1_d14263e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Declaration:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">trigger formatToDisplay</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Applies to:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lym1665702585074.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lym1665702585074.html\" title=\"A Field is a Development Object that represents a unit of data in an Entity. This could represent a column in a DBMS table or data that is not stored in the database, such as a derived field or a user interface control. Its associated properties define the way it is stored, its GUI representation, and default behavior.\">Field</a>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Activation:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Activated when the form is initially displayed, each time an occurrence becomes active, after the loseFocus trigger, and after the formatFromDisplay trigger to restore the value of <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$format</span>.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Default behavior:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n None\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Behavior upon completion:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n None\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jok1665703129463__section_w491ab1b7b3_w492ab1b7_w493ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d807562e132\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jok1665703129463__p_d116285e1_d116286e1_d116287e1\">The formatToDisplay trigger is used to convert data from the internal format used by Uniface to an external (displayed or printed) format. It is activated whenever Uniface needs to display the field.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jok1665703129463__p_d116288e1_d116289e1_d116290e1\">The formatToDisplay and formatFromDisplay triggers are especially useful with custom widgets. Any ValRep mapping for widgets happens after formatToDisplay and before formatFromDisplay.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"jok1665703129463__note_w494ab1b7b3b7_w495ab1b7b3_w496ab1b7_w497ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The formatFromDisplay trigger should undo the formatting done\n            here.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jok1665703129463__p_d116291e1_d116292e1_d116293e1\">When the trigger is activated, the function <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$format</span> contains the data. This data has been formatted according to the display (DIS) property of the field's layout definition. You may use ProcScript or 3GL code to modify the data in <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$format</span> before it is displayed. When the trigger completes, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$format</span> should contain the data formatted for display.</p>\n<div class=\"note caution note_caution\" id=\"jok1665703129463__note_w498ab1b7b3c11_w499ab1b7b3_w500ab1b7_w501ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">CAUTION:</span> The formatToDisplay trigger should be used only for formatting of the\n            associated field. Do not use this trigger for formatting other fields or for other\n            field-related processing. </div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jok1665703129463__p_d116294e1_d116295e1_d116296e1\">While a component is being populated, a field's formatToDisplay trigger may be activated in several occurrences. During this activity, the occurrence that is current in the form remains unchanged. This means that if you reference another field from the formatToDisplay trigger, you always reference that field in the current occurrence, which is not necessarily the same occurrence as the field whose formatToDisplay trigger is being activated.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/deb1665702681553.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>trigger formatFromDisplay</a><p>System trigger that temporarily converts the format of data in a field from an external format into an internal format, and makes that reformatted data available for processing purposes.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528971\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528971\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "trigger formatToDisplay Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 17, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 trigger formatToDisplay System trigger that temporarily converts the format of data in a field from an internal format into an external format that is displayed or printed. Declaration: trigger formatToDisplay Applies to: Field Activation: Activated when the form is initially displayed, each time an occurrence becomes active, after the loseFocus trigger, and after the formatFromDisplay trigger to restore the value of $format . Default behavior: None Behavior upon completion: None Description The formatToDisplay trigger is used to convert data from the internal format used by Uniface to an external (displayed or printed) format. It is activated whenever Uniface needs to display the field. The formatToDisplay and formatFromDisplay triggers are especially useful with custom widgets. Any ValRep mapping for widgets happens after formatToDisplay and before formatFromDisplay. Note: The formatFromDisplay trigger should undo the formatting done here. When the trigger is activated, the function $format contains the data. This data has been formatted according to the display (DIS) property of the field's layout definition. You may use ProcScript or 3GL code to modify the data in $format before it is displayed. When the trigger completes, $format should contain the data formatted for display. CAUTION: The formatToDisplay trigger should be used only for formatting of the associated field. Do not use this trigger for formatting other fields or for other field-related processing. While a component is being populated, a field's formatToDisplay trigger may be activated in several occurrences. During this activity, the occurrence that is current in the form remains unchanged. This means that if you reference another field from the formatToDisplay trigger, you always reference that field in the current occurrence, which is not necessarily the same occurrence as the field whose formatToDisplay trigger is being activated. Related Links trigger formatFromDisplay System trigger that temporarily converts the format of data in a field from an external format into an internal format, and makes that reformatted data available for processing purposes. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}